news.title: New York City office leasing surges; still below pre-pandemic levels
news.para: Office leasing volume rose 27.6% to 9.23 million square feet, the strongest quarterly gain since the end of 2019 - a gangbuster year for leasing in New York, according to Colliers International Group Inc.

news.title: Australia's 'Big Four' lenders raise home loan rates in step with central bank
news.para: The move is in sync with the country's central bank, which earlier in the day raised its benchmark lending rate by 25 basis points. Australian banks have so far followed the steps of the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) in raising borrowing costs.

news.title: NGT directs Express Builders to pay Rs 15 crore compensation for illegal construction
news.para: ​​The green panel was hearing a petition against the violation of EC conditions by Express Builders and Promoters Private Limited in constructing 'Express Zenith' at Sector 77 in Noida.

news.title: Delhi RERA seeks pollution exemption for projects
news.para: The move comes after the CII Delhi Sub-committee on Real Estate and the Confederation of Real Estate Developers' Associations of India (CREDAI)-NCR submitted a representation to RERA of Delhi, UP and Gurgaon to exempt projects from the construction ban.

news.title: Indore: Over 40 residential structures to be razed for STP in Devnagar
news.para: He said that an STP with 35mld capacity has been planned in the area and work on the same is scheduled to be started after the Diwali festival.

news.title: Demolition drive will resume after Dasara: Karnataka revenue minister
news.para: Revenue minister R Ashoka, who held a meeting with BBMP and revenue department officials on Monday, said the drive was stopped because of festivities.

news.title: Nagpur: PMAY beneficiaries told to pay annual GP tax, ground rent to NIT
news.para: PMAY beneficiaries of Tarodi (khurd) Housing Scheme have started to get demand notes from NIT to pay the annual ground rent.

news.title: Mohali civic body collects Rs 22.1 crore property tax during Apr-Sept 2022
news.para: “It is a record achievement. From April 1 to September 30, 2021, the collection was only Rs 14.25 crore,” said MC commissioner Navjot Kaur.

news.title: Nashik zilla parishad provides homes under PMAY
news.para: The G+1-storey housing is being carried out by the ZP for beneficiaries of schemes as they are unable to get land for construction of houses.

news.title: Greater Noida: Himalaya Pride residents allege tower E blocks walkway
news.para: GNIDA additional CEO Amandeep Duli said, "The tower appears illegal to me. However, the head of planning will make a report after a visit to the society and give it to me on Tuesday. Based on it, GNIDA will take action -- seal the tower or impose a penalty on the builder."

news.title: Infrastructure, construction, realty join sectors like financials in better credit ratios
news.para: Crisil said that  nearly 80% of its ratings in the first half of the fiscal did not change but the rate of upgrades improved to 16.70% from around 14% in the second half of last fiscal and up from about 3% two years ago. The downgrade rate on the other hand was flat at 3.02%.

news.title: Why are sports cities in Noida delayed? Firm to find out
news.para: Between 2014 and 2017, the Authority had allotted around 34 lakh sqm to four developers in sectors 78, 79, 101, 150 and 152.

news.title: Gurugram: NBCC Green View buyers meet deputy commissioner seeking refund
news.para: The buyers alleged that the developer hasn’t complied with the district administration’s order asking NBCC India to refund the amount paid by allottees towards their flats, along with applicable interest, as per the law.

news.title: Housing societies oppose repeal of MOFA, say MahaRERA not always helpful
news.para: Nearly 1.25 lakh cooperative housing societies are registered in Maharashtra. More than 60% of these societies have not received conveyance from the builders.

news.title: Mumbai: Mhada takes over eight acres of Juhu plot from SRA builder
news.para: While Mhada has taken 'paper possession' of the plot, the developer, Bombay Slum Redevelopment Corporation Ltd, said there was a Bombay high court stay on the possession notice.
